<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A motorist who had just refuelled their car has had a lucky escape after a milk tanker lost control and crashed into a petrol station.</p>

<p>The truck was travelling through Traralgon in Victoria's Gippsland region early Friday morning when the driver lost control on a bend.</p>

<p>The truck veered over a centre median strip, cleaned up a set of traffic lights and careered into a petrol station.</p>

<p>The vehicle then struck a car parked at the petrol bowser before coming to a stop metres away from the shopfront.</p>

<p>This milk tanker was extensively damaged after it lost control and crashed into a petrol station</p>

<p>Photos of the crash aftermath show extensive damage to the smashed up milk truck and how narrowly close it came to smashing into the shopfront.</p>

<p>The petrol bowser was also extensively damaged. </p>

<p>No one was seriously injured in the crash.</p>

<p>A motorist who was filling up their car at the boswer moments earlier inside the shop paying at the time.</p>

<p>The truck driver aged in his 40s was taken to hospital with non-life-threatening injuries.</p>

<p>The milk tanker came to a stop metres away from hitting the petrol station shopfront</p>

<p>The main road through Traralgon was closed for the rest of the night with westbound traffic on Princess Street completely blocked.</p>

<p>East bound traffic on Princes Street was down to one lane as heavy haulage operators spent the night clearing the scene.</p>

<p>Police believe the truck was travelling from the nearby town of Churchill.</p>

<p>Anyone with more information and or dashcam vision of the truck is urged to call Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000.</p>

<p>The milk truck driver was taken to hospital with minor injuries. Pictured is the tanker wreckage</p>
